DESCRIPTION:
Verify that an order cannot be created without valid access token.
Expected result: HTTP 401 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "You should be authorised" in response body.
NAME: Should return 401 when creating an order with valid required fields but without an access token.

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user cannot be registered without a password.
Expected result: HTTP 403 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "Email, password and name are required fields" in response body.
NAME: Should return 403 when registering a user without a password

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user can be registered with valid required fields.
Expected result: HTTP 200 response, previously introduced data in the fields "email" and "name", the "accessToken" and "refreshToken" fields in the response body contain non-null values.
NAME: Should return 200 when registering a user with valid required fields

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user can log in with valid required fields.
Expected result: HTTP 200 response, The fields "email" and "name" contain data entered by the user when registering, the "accessToken" and "refreshToken" fields in the response body contain non-null values.
NAME: Should return 200 when logging in a user with valid required fields

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user cannot be registered without an email.
Expected result: HTTP 403 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "Email, password and name are required fields" in response body.
NAME: Should return 403 when registering a user without an email

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user cannot be logged in without email
Expected result: HTTP 401 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "email or password are incorrect" in response body.
NAME: Should return 200 when logging in a user without email

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that registering a user twice with the same data fails.
Expected result: HTTP 403 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "User already exists" in response body.
NAME: Should return 409 when trying to create two identical users

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user cannot be registered without a name.
Expected result: HTTP 403 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "Email, password and name are required fields" in response body.
NAME: Should return 403 when registering a user without a name

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that a user cannot be logged in without password
Expected result: HTTP 401 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "email or password are incorrect" in response body.
NAME: Should return 200 when logging in a user without password

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that an order cannot be created without ingredients.
Expected result: HTTP 400 response, response field "success" - false and an error message "Ingredient ids must be provided" in response body.
NAME: Should return 400 when creating an order without ingredients.

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that an order can be created with valid required fields and a valid access token.
Expected result: HTTP 200 response, response field "success" - true, the "name" and "number" fields in the response body contain non-null values.
NAME: Should return 200 when creating an order with valid required fields and a valid access token.

DESCRIPTION:
Verify that an order cannot be created with an invalid ingredient hash.
Expected result: HTTP 500 response.
NAME: Should return 500 when creating an order with an invalid ingredient hash.
